<p>I was looking through Log4J docs and stumbled at the following in the description of <a href="https://logging.apache.org/log4j/1.2/apidocs/org/apache/log4j/Category.html#setLevel(org.apache.log4j.Level)" rel="nofollow"><code>Logger#setLevel()</code></a> (inherited from <code>Category</code>) method:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>If you are passing any of <code>Level.DEBUG</code>, <code>Level.INFO</code>, <code>Level.WARN</code>,   <code>Level.ERROR</code>, <code>Level.FATAL</code> as a parameter, you need to case them as   <code>Level</code>. As in</p>  <pre><code>logger.setLevel((Level) Level.DEBUG); </code></pre> </blockquote>  <p>Is there any reason behind such requirement?  </p>  <p>Am I missing something here?</p>